title: Ali El-Kaf
text:
Ali Mohammed El-Kaf El-Sayed (; born 15 June 1906, 1979) was an <a href="Egyptians">Egyptian</a> <a href="association%20football">football</a> <a href="Defender%20%28association%20football%29">defender</a> who played for <a href="Egypt%20national%20football%20team">Egypt</a> in the <a href="1934%20FIFA%20World%20Cup">1934 FIFA World Cup</a>. He also played for <a href="Zamalek%20SC">Zamalek SC</a>, and represented Egypt at the <a href="1936%20Summer%20Olympics">1936 Summer Olympics</a>.
International career.
He represented <a href="Egypt%20national%20football%20team">Egypt</a> in the <a href="1934%20FIFA%20World%20Cup">1934 FIFA World Cup</a> and <a href="Football%20at%20the%201936%20Summer%20Olympics">1936 Summer Olympics</a>.
